<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{x}-{5}{y}={18}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{7}{y}={39}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},-{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+-{5}{y}={18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}={18}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{18}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{\left(\frac{{{18}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{1}}}}\right)}+-{7}{y}={39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{6}}{{-{{1}}}}\cdot{\left({18}\right)}--\frac{{6}}{{-{{1}}}}{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}={39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{108}-{\left({30}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}={39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{30}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}={39}-{108}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{30}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}=-{69}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({30}+{\left(-{7}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{69}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{23}{y}=-{69}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{69}}{{23}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+-{5}{\left(-{3}\right)}={18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+{\left({15}\right)}={18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}={18}-{\left({15}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}={3}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{3}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},-{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

